; The synced web/package-lock.json (byte-identical to Marcuss-ops/VeloxFrontend@HEAD)
; pins @eslint/js at ^10.0.1 which peer-requires eslint@^10.0.0, but it also pins
; eslint at ^9.39.3. Without this flag `npm ci` refuses to install the tree.
;
; This peer-set is a real upstream shape (eslint 9 + @eslint/js 10 coexist in
; practice because the @eslint/js major bumped ahead of the eslint major).
; Tracking the synced lockfile faithfully is more important than passing strict
; peer resolution here — the SPA build still works on eslint 9 because the
; runtime / vite plugin don't load eslint. So `legacy-peer-deps=true` is the
; least-disruptive fix that keeps the lockfile byte-identical and lets
; `npm ci` succeed.
legacy-peer-deps=true
